            <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

            <p>Please note that if you would like to report any bugs or glitches in our software, visit our <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://github.com/Mooonys">GitHub</a> page. You may also notify us with your suggestions
                via the <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/Mooonys/Mooonys/discussions">GitHub</a> page and/or our <a
                    target="_blank" href="{{URL 'collaboration/feedback'}}">Feedback</a> page.</p>

            <div class="text-divider"></div>

            <section id="cookies">
                <h1 class="text-md color-contrast-high">How we use cookies?</h1>

                <p class="color-contrast-high">
                    When you visit Acolytes, we put small files (known as ‘cookies’) onto your computer to collect
                    information about how you browse the site.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Cookies are used to measure how you use the website so it can be updated and improved based on
                    your needs, we also store smaller files as cookies onto your system to track when you log into our
                    site to create a more ease of access when using Acolytes.

                    <p>Find out more about <a class="color-primary" target="_blank"
                            href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/online/cookies/">how to manage
                            cookies</a>.</p>
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="text-divider"></div>

            <section id="newsletter">
                <h1 class="text-md color-contrast-high">How we use your email address?</h1>

                <p class="color-contrast-high">
                    When you subscribe to our newsletter, we send you emails using a local webserver module called
                    <a class="color-primary" target="_blank" href="https://nodemailer.com/about/">Nodemailer</a>.
                    Therefore, we will
                    never have to share
                    your email address with other third parties. Your newsletter information will be used for the
                    sole purpose of sending
                    you relevant emails about Updates and/or new Features regarding Acolytes.
                </p>

                <p>
                    When you wish to unsubscribe from our
                    newsletter, you can do that by clicking the 'unsubscribe' link in the footer of each newsletter.

                    <p>Find out more about <a class="color-primary" target="_blank"
                            href="https://nodemailer.com/about/">how we send
                            you emails</a>.</p>
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="text-divider"></div>

            <section id="database">
                <h1 class="text-md color-contrast-high">How we store your information?</h1>

                <p class="color-contrast-high">
                    When you register on our website we store all your responded information into a <a
                        class="color-primary" target="_blank" href="https://www.mongodb.com/">MongoDB</a> database, this
                    allows us to get information from the database regarding your account like your password or
                    username that will be used to verify your credentials when you next login. We also store
                    information like your email address and settings on our database which all goes towards saving
                    and collecting your specific and relevant options.
                </p>

                <p>
                    When we send your information to our database we are the only people who can then recieve that
                    information. When we request information regarding your account on the database we only store
                    and collect information that creates an easier and more enjoyable experience for you.

                    <p>Find out more about <a class="color-primary" target="_blank" href="https://www.mongodb.com/">how
                            we store
                            your information</a>.</p>
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="text-divider"></div>

            <p class="color-contrast-high">
                Are you still unsure about your privacy when using Acolytes?
            </p>

